# 🤖 SECTION 1 — Data Engineering Mindset

## 🧠 The Reality of Real-World Machine Learning

Welcome to Day 1 of the 45-Day ML Engineering Roadmap.

Before we write a single line of predictive logic or build a neural network, we must address the most overlooked truth in Artificial Intelligence: **Algorithms do not create knowledge; they extract it.** If you feed a state-of-the-art Deep Learning model with messy, biased, or broken data, it will confidently output messy, biased, and broken predictions. By the end of this section, you will develop a strict "Data-First" engineering mindset, understanding exactly how real-world data is structured, broken down, and prepared for machine consumption.

### 🎯 Learning Objectives

* Understand why the industry is shifting toward **Data-Centric AI**.
* Deconstruct the anatomy of a real-world dataset.
* Identify the critical differences between data structures (Structured, Unstructured, Time-Series).
* Spot devastating data quality issues, including the silent killer: **Data Leakage**.
* Map the end-to-end data preparation pipeline.

