## 2. Understanding Data Formats

The digital world generates quintillions of bytes of data daily, but it arrives in drastically different formats.

| Data Type | Description | Ease of ML Processing | Real-World Examples |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Structured** | Highly organized, neatly fits into rows and columns (Relational). | Very Easy (Standard ML) | Excel files, SQL tables, CSVs, Financial ledgers. |
| **Semi-structured** | Contains tags or markers to separate elements, but lacks a strict tabular schema. | Moderate | JSON files, XML, HTML, NoSQL databases. |
| **Unstructured** | Raw, heavy, human-centric data with no predefined format. | Difficult (Requires Deep Learning/NLP) | Images, audio files, YouTube videos, raw text PDFs. |

