## 5. The Data Pipeline Overview

In industry, data does not arrive ready for modeling. It must flow through an automated pipeline.

```text
Data Collection      (Scraping APIs, querying SQL databases)
      ↓
Storage              (Data Lakes, Data Warehouses)
      ↓
Cleaning             (Handling missing values, fixing typos)
      ↓
Feature Engineering  (Creating new metrics, mathematically scaling inputs)
      ↓
EDA                  (Visualizing trends, understanding distributions)
      ↓
Model Training       (Feeding the clean data to the algorithm)
      ↓
Deployment           (Serving predictions to real users)

```

