## 🎤 Interview Questions

**Q1. Explain the concept of Data-Centric AI versus Model-Centric AI.**
**Answer:** Model-centric AI focuses on keeping the dataset fixed while tweaking the algorithm's architecture and hyperparameters to improve accuracy. Data-centric AI keeps the model architecture relatively fixed while focusing on systematically improving the quality, cleanliness, and labeling of the dataset, which often yields higher real-world performance.

**Q2. What is Data Leakage, and how does it affect a Machine Learning model?**
**Answer:** Data leakage occurs when future or target-revealing information accidentally leaks into the training dataset. It causes the model to show artificially high accuracy during training and evaluation, but fail catastrophically in production because that "leaked" information will not be available at inference time.

**Q3. If an algorithm is performing poorly, what is the first thing you should investigate?**
**Answer:** The data. Following the GIGO (Garbage In, Garbage Out) principle, I would check for missing values, massive outliers, mislabeled targets, or noisy data before ever attempting to switch to a more complex algorithmic architecture.

